            <div class="article-feature-caption hide-on-tablet">
        <p class="photo-credit">Kameleon007/iStock</p>
	      				<p>Harvard Medical School has been awarded a $100 million grant from the National Football League Players Association to create a 10-year initiative for the study of injuries. “Our goal is to transform the health of these athletes,” said Lee Nadler, HMS dean for clinical and translational research.</p>
			        </div><!--/.article-feature-caption-->
        
    
			
